# Beartropy Tables - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This project uses **Beartropy Tables**, a Livewire data table component for the TALL stack (Tailwind, Alpine, Laravel, Livewire).

## Table Architecture

### Base Class
All tables extend `Beartropy\Tables\BeartropyTable` (a Livewire component):

```php
use Beartropy\Tables\BeartropyTable;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Columns\Column;

class MyTable extends BeartropyTable
{
    public $model = \App\Models\MyModel::class;

    public function columns(): array
    {
        return [
            Column::make('Name', 'name')->sortable()->searchable(),
        ];
    }
}
```

### Two Data Modes
```php
# Model-based (Eloquent)
public $model = User::class;

# Array-based (no model)
public function data(): array
{
    return [['id' => 1, 'name' => 'Foo']];
}
```

## Column Types

```php
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Columns\Column;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Columns\BoolColumn;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Columns\DateColumn;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Columns\LinkColumn;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Columns\ToggleColumn;

# Basic
Column::make('Name', 'name')->sortable()->searchable()

# Boolean
BoolColumn::make('Verified', 'email_verified_at')
    ->trueIs(fn($v) => !is_null($v))->centered()

# Date
DateColumn::make('Created', 'created_at')
    ->outputFormat('M d, Y')->sortable()

# Link
LinkColumn::make('Email', 'email')
    ->href(fn($row) => "mailto:{$row->email}")

# Toggle
ToggleColumn::make('Active', 'is_active')
    ->disableToggleWhen(fn($row) => !auth()->user()->can('update', $row))
```

## Filter Types

```php
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Filters\FilterString;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Filters\FilterSelect;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Filters\FilterBool;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Filters\FilterDateRange;
use Beartropy\Tables\Classes\Filters\FilterSelectMagic;

# Text search
FilterString::make('Name', 'name')

# Select dropdown
FilterSelect::make('Status', ['pending', 'approved', 'rejected'], 'status')

# Boolean toggle
FilterBool::make('Active', null, 'is_active')

# Date range
FilterDateRange::make('Created', 'created_at')

# Auto-populated select
FilterSelectMagic::make('Role', 'role')
```

## Key Table Properties

```php
public $model = User::class;           // Eloquent model (null for array)
public array $with = ['profile'];       // Eager load
public string $column_id = 'id';        // Primary key
public bool $with_pagination = true;    // Pagination
public bool $has_bulk = false;          // Bulk selection
public bool $has_counter = true;        // Row counter
public bool $useGlobalSearch = true;    // Global search
public bool $show_column_toggle = true; // Column visibility toggle
public bool $useCards = false;          // Card layout
public bool $showCardsOnMobile = false; // Cards on mobile
public bool $sticky_header = false;     // Sticky header
```

## Fluent Column Methods

```php
Column::make('Label', 'index')
    ->sortable()                    // Enable sorting
    ->searchable()                  // Enable searching
    ->editable('select', $options)  // Inline editing
    ->setUpdateField('db_field')    // Different DB field
    ->pushLeft() / ->pushRight() / ->centered()  // Alignment
    ->customData(fn($row) => ...)   // Transform data
    ->view('custom.view')           // Custom Blade view
    ->styling('text-red-500')       // TD CSS classes
    ->hideWhen(!$isAdmin)           // Conditional visibility
    ->hideFromSelector()            // Hide from column toggle
    ->toHtml()                      // Raw HTML output
    ->hideOnMobile()                // Hide on mobile
    ->collapseOnMobile()            // Collapse on mobile
    ->cardTitle()                   // Card title
    ->showOnCard()                  // Show in card view
```

## Custom Query Callbacks

```php
# Custom sort
Column::make('Priority', 'priority')
    ->sortable(function ($query, $direction) {
        $query->orderByRaw("FIELD(priority, 'high', 'medium', 'low') $direction");
    })

# Custom search
Column::make('Full Name')
    ->customData(fn($row) => $row->first_name . ' ' . $row->last_name)
    ->searchable(function ($query, $term) {
        $query->where('first_name', 'like', "%$term%")
              ->orWhere('last_name', 'like', "%$term%");
    })

# Custom filter query (receives $query, $value, $filter)
FilterSelect::make('Type', ['recent', 'archived'], 'type')
    ->query(function ($query, $value) {
        return match ($value) {
            'recent' => $query->recent(),
            'archived' => $query->archived(),
            default => $query,
        };
    })
```

## Dot Notation for Relationships

```php
# Column — auto-resolves belongsTo/hasOne
Column::make('Bio', 'profile.bio')->sortable()->searchable()

# Filter — auto-applies whereHas()
FilterString::make('Bio', 'profile.bio')

# For hasMany — use customData + custom callbacks
Column::make('Theme', 'theme_setting')
    ->customData(fn($row) => $row->settings->firstWhere('key', 'theme')?->value)
    ->sortable(fn($query, $dir) => $query->orderBy(...))
    ->searchable(fn($query, $term) => $query->orWhereHas(...))
```

## Inline Editing

```php
# Basic
Column::make('Name', 'name')->editable()

# Select
Column::make('Status', 'status')
    ->editable('select', [
        ['value' => 'draft', 'label' => 'Draft'],
        ['value' => 'published', 'label' => 'Published'],
    ])

# With callback
Column::make('Priority', 'priority')
    ->editable('select', $options, 'handlePriorityUpdate')

# Authorization (override in table class)
public function authorizeFieldUpdate(Model $record, string $field, mixed $value): bool
{
    return auth()->user()->can('update', $record);
}
```

## Blade Usage

```blade
{{-- Standard --}}
<livewire:users-table />

{{-- Show only table (no wrapper) --}}
<livewire:products-table :show-only-table="true" />
```

## Rules for Code Generation

1. **Always extend `BeartropyTable`** for table components
2. **Always implement `columns()`** — it is required
3. **Set `$model`** for Eloquent tables, or implement `data()` for array tables
4. **Use `$with`** to eager load relationships
5. **Use dot notation** for simple relationship columns/filters
6. **Use `customData()` + custom callbacks** for hasMany relationships
7. **Use `sortable()` and `searchable()`** on key columns
8. **Use `FilterSelectMagic`** when options come from distinct values
9. **Override `authorizeFieldUpdate()`** for inline editing security
10. **Never build table components from scratch** — extend BeartropyTable

## Don't Suggest

- Custom table HTML when Beartropy Tables can handle it
- Manual pagination logic (use `$with_pagination`)
- Manual search implementation (use `searchable()`)
- Manual sort logic (use `sortable()`)
- Raw database queries for filtering (use Filter classes)

## Do Suggest

- Extending `BeartropyTable` for all data tables
- Appropriate column types (BoolColumn, DateColumn, etc.)
- Filter types matching the data (FilterString, FilterSelect, etc.)
- Dot notation for relationship data
- Mobile-responsive options (`showCardsOnMobile`, `hideOnMobile`)
- Inline editing with authorization

## Quick Reference

Need help? Reference: `vendor/beartropy/tables/docs/ai-assistants/BEARTROPY_GUIDE.md`

---

**When generating table code, ALWAYS extend BeartropyTable and use the provided column/filter classes.**
